E
clearing holy place grove~
Lush, dark grass lies in a soft carpet across the floor of this circular
clearing.  The thick trunks of oaks bend slightly toward the center of
the grove's open space, giving them the appearance of attending
solitiously to the holiness of the well and the worshippers who come here
to pray and meditate.  Light moves softly across the wind-teased grass,
causing warm patches of brilliance to dance atop the shaded clearing
floor.
~
E
light patches~
Warm, dusky light pushes its way through the thick branches and
whispering leaves of the ancient oaks to dot the floor of this holy place
in pale patches of warmth.  All along the well and surrounding grass,
patterns of light move in a quick dance that mesmerizes you.  The water
bubbling to the top of the sacred spring ripples gently with the subtle
force of the wind, causing the light to reflect upwards and mirror
shining patterns onto the underside of the leafy canopy above.
~
E
well spring pool sacred~
Flat, grey stones stacked tightly together form the sides of the circular
well.  Within its walls, water from a natural spring bubbles to the top,
cold and clear and free of impurities.  Water leaks out from between some
of the rocks and is carried down a narrow channel worn into the soft
earth during the course of many years.  The ground around the well is not
muddy; rather, it is covered with a thick, plush carpet of fine grasses
and clover.  Upon one of the rocks that create the sides of the well lies
a single pear, cut from top to bottom to expose the rich, white flesh,
the dark seeds and pale veins inside.
~
E
pear fruit vein flesh seeds~
Cut from top to bottom, the pear's juicy flesh lies open for inspection. 
You see the dark seeds lying in stark contrast to the heavy whiteness of
the fruit.  Threading through the white fruit are pale brown veins which,
when the pear is cut open this way, resemble an upside-down heart shape.
