oak trees that have started to encroach on the older corners of the
orchard.  One small pear sapling grows among the taller, intrusive oaks,
which seem to bend over the little tree protectively.  Beyond the oaks,
you hear the muted sounds of woodland animals as they move on the bed of
dried leaves on the forest floor.
